==English==
===Etymology===
After [[w:Edwin Hubble|Edwin Powell Hubble]], American astronomer
===Noun===
'''Hubble law'''
#{{astronomy}} states that the [[velocity]] at which a [[distant]] object is [[receeding]] from the [[Earth]] (as measured by its [[redshift]]) is proportional to its [[distance]]; [[observational]] [[evidence]] for an [[expanding]] [[universe]]
===Alternative spellings===
*[[Hubble's law]]
===Related terms===
*[[Hubble constant]]
